title: Sultanahmet Camii
description: The Sultanahmet Camii (The Blue/Sultan Ahmed Mosque) was built on the primary site of the Great Palace of Constantinople between 1609 and 1616 during the rule of Ahmed I.

properties.description: Point representing the location of Sultanahmet Camii (The Blue/Sultan Ahmed Mosque), constructed on the primary site of the Great Palace of Constantinople, derived from an OpenStreetMap Node.
